// Street, Drainage and Building Act 1974 [Act 133] — PBT street-level
// enforcement: s46 (obstruction of public places — stalls, goods, building
// materials, and s46(1)(g) a vehicle resting on a footway; warrantless arrest
// by police OR authorized council officers; fine ≤RM500, repeat ≤RM1,000),
// s124 (must give name/address when charged by an officer), s125 (arrest ONLY
// if name/address unknown/refused/doubted; detention no longer than needed to
// bring before a court), s127 (general penalty ceiling RM10,000 + RM500/day).
// AUTHORITY: PBT (enforced by local authorities; s46/s125 also empower police —
// single-authority field limitation, tagged PBT as primary).
// SCOPE: Peninsular Malaysia only (state:"PENINSULAR").
